        <td bgcolor="black" colspan="2"  valign="top">
		<img src="icon_posticon.gif" border="0" hspace="3"><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/05/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 06:09:05</font>

		&nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&amp;id=3559"><img src="icon_profile.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Show Profile" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>
 
			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=3559')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&amp;TOPIC_ID=4525&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=My+Patch+Message+Summary+%2D+6%2F5%2F2002"><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> For completeness I'll move the non-essential stuff, for us, to the bottom.  </P><P>June 5th, 2002 3:00 am <BR>------------------------------ </P><P>** Acrylia Caverns ** </P><P>- The Chieftain has gone on a vacation. We're retuning this encounter, and beg your indulgence while we work on it. (cause ya know.. they haven't fucked with AC enough)</P><P><BR>** Spells ** </P><P>- Fixed magician summoned focus earrings (it used to lower mana usage... now what?)<BR>- Characters on horses are no longer immune to Ignite Bones (does this mean we can cast the spell on horse back now too?)<BR>- The Shadowbond series of spells can no longer be dispelled by the Necromancer </P><P><BR>** Items ** </P><P>- Added 'focus' effects to over 150 existing items (/sigh - let me know when focus 3 items are out... k thx)<BR>- The key to the Plane of Air should now disappear when the character leaves the plane (/mourn)<BR>- Fixed Sifaye, Owlbear Feather, Grimling fang and Rockhopper talon darts to use the Throwing skill rather than the Archery skill (Throwing(10)!  - all I have to say. :) )<BR>- Added a 4 second casting time to Golem Metal Wand  (erm.. PvP benifits/nerfs right?  Never touched them)<BR>- Added a 3 second casting time on Egg Shaped Pumice (ditto)<BR>- Added a 4 second casting time to Oil of Fennin Ro (ditto)</P><P><BR>** NPCs ** </P><P>- NPC casters should be a little bit smarter now. They will choose their spells a little more carefully. (nfi...)</P><P><BR>** Quests ** </P><P>- Arbogast and Miller should be responding properly now (happily I was indifferent to this guy.. there was like 8 of him up the last time I was huntting in Katta.. wonder if this is fixed)<BR>- Fixed spawns in the Grey for Beastlord Epic (fyi for those hunting in the grey.. enjoy the traps) <BR>- Made several adjustments that should fix issues with the 10th ring war (damn you who are at this level.. /drool ring)</P><P><BR>** Tradeskills ** </P><P>- Made some changes to the General Blacksmithing difficulties to make the progression in this trade skill more logical and to allow for more variety in that path (my translation: harder to get smithing skill ups)<BR>- Added more than 200 smithing recipes <BR>- Enchanted Clay is now stackable <BR>- Sheet of Fiery Metal, Essence of Fire, Imp Blood, and Fiery Temper are now stackable <BR>- Enchanted HQ Ore can now be worked into rings, jointing, sheets, bricks, and blocks in a standard forge </P><P><BR>** Pet Changes ** </P><P>With this patch we've made some rather sweeping changes to the way pets work. </P><P>- Pets will not attack mesmerized creatures. Pets basically treat mesmerized NPCs as if they were dead (and no, you cannot break a mezzed npc with your pet)<BR>- Pets are neutral to NPCs. Monsters will not attack pets first unless the pet is being aggressive to something (what if your pet is off wandering, and sometihng jumps you.  Your pet then becomes agressive towards whatever is attacking you - will this then make it no longer beta-neutral?  hmm.)<BR>- Pets take 75% of the experience from a creature if no player does damage to that creature <BR>- Pets take ZERO experience from a creature unless no player does damage to that creature (Yay!)<BR>- The exception to the above rule is Dire Charmed pets, which will take a share of the experience scaled by the amount of damage they do. In most situations (with an active party, for example) the Dire Charmed pet will not take experience. Like all pets, they will take 75% of the experience if no PC does damage to the target. As long as a player does damage to a creature, a Dire Charmed pet will never take more experience than it used to. (See this <a href="http://necro.eqclasses.com/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=4522" target="_blank">http://necro.eqclasses.com/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=4522</a> post for a good breakdown)</P><P>- Charmed NPCs will now respond to the /pet report health command (/shrug - like I use this)<BR>- /pet sit down command should now work on charmed NPCs  (um.. it worked before.. but after 20 seconds they pathed off like they were bored)</P><P></P><P>** Miscellaneous ** </P><P>- Fixed a bug that was causing a person that logs out with "damage shields: OFF" to be unable to see damage shield even when they turned them back on <BR>- Fixed a problem that was causing crashes when /following someone on a horse if they went out of range (happened to me a few times..)<BR>- Fixed a bug that prevented targeting an invisible NPC from horseback, even with See Invisible (damnit, bring back my ability to target "A Mystic Voice" please - I rather enjoyed looking like I was kicking the Nexus Scions arse)</P><P></P><P>--(And now for the list I could care less about)--</P><P><BR>** Spells **<BR>- Nature's melody and Song of the Deep Seas should now stack with Dance of the Blades </P><P>** Items **<BR>- Mischievous Chainmail armor is now Dwarf wearable (for those lil Bristlbane worshipin' dorf rogues) <BR>- Keys for Veeshan's Peak, Sleeper's Tomb, Vex Thal are now no-drop on the Firiona Vie server <BR>- Changed several of the new cultural chain skirts from Leg slot to Waist slot <BR>- The effect from Hammer of the Sun (Dawncall) now has a longer range <BR>- Fixed it so you can't fire fishing grubs with a bow (we know this had a lot of you worried...) <BR>- Smithed Acrylia Chain and Plate armors are now magical </P><P>** Quests **<BR>- Sir Lucan's skeleton should be available again <BR>- The Neriak Initiate Breastplate recipe should now work <BR>- Freeport Monk Guild Master Klom Jyson should be responding now </P><P>** Pet Changes **<BR>- Fixed a bug that was preventing reclaim energy from working on Magician Epic pets.</P><P></P><P>EDIT: Damnit, no html allow.  So much for links.</P><P><BR>Edited by - Suith on 06/05/2002  06:14:08</font></td>

      </tr>

